              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29458352-naksed?shelf=martyr-heroine">martyr-heroine</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29458352-naksed?shelf=martyr-hero">martyr-hero</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2032974825&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2032974825" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer370043120540506294">The reviews are glowing, the sample was intriguing and Mary Balogh is a great writer. However, the subject (destitution, prostitution, adultery, etc.) is too bleak for me, at least at th e present time. I want to escape into a light, frothy confection, not endure self-flagellation and revulsion. So I will pass on this. At least for now.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


