<span id="freeTextContainer4765795828380745643">3 for the romance . Fleur and Adam. Trigger warnings: Adam is already married. He cheats on his wife with Fleur who is so desperate that she is starting a new career as a prostitute . I did not like the author rewriting history by having Adam say that he loved her from the beginning. If he loved her from the beginning why did he have angry sex that was so rough without kissing Fleur for their first time. He also cheats on his wife (the wife has never had sex with him and cheats on him) with Fleu</span>
  <span id="freeText4765795828380745643" style="display:none">3 for the romance . Fleur and Adam. Trigger warnings: Adam is already married. He cheats on his wife with Fleur who is so desperate that she is starting a new career as a prostitute . I did not like the author rewriting history by having Adam say that he loved her from the beginning. If he loved her from the beginning why did he have angry sex that was so rough without kissing Fleur for their first time. He also cheats on his wife (the wife has never had sex with him and cheats on him) with Fleur after he fall in love with her. <br />I also did not like how the author turned Fleurs fear of Adam because of the rough, course sexual experience as a virgin and implied that Fleur thought the fear emotion was love and she just did not recognize it at first toward the end of the story. In the beginning that fear was fear. Later, she fell in love but the original fear was not love. Imho. The hero was right about that.<br />These dark "gothic" feel stories with a smidgeon of romance are not my cup of tea, but I have to admit that this was well written. However, it was an over the top, eye rolling, lets not even give this sad story an uplifting epilogue.<br />My favorite part of this book is how well the title matches the secret in the story.<br />Edited to add: Just read A Mask of Deception and this one is better than that one so bumped this up to 3.25 stars.</span>
