              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=historical-ye-ole-blighty">historical-ye-ole-blighty</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=adorable-sidekicks">adorable-sidekicks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=insta-family">insta-family</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=the-oldest-profession">the-oldest-profession</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=potayto-potahto">potayto-potahto</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=never-been-there-before">never-been-there-before</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=one-true-pairing">one-true-pairing</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=3-star-reads">3-star-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9969735-unusualchild-beppy?shelf=no-one-in-between">no-one-in-between</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer341754159" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4258393486388175481">3 stars<br/><br/>I find that I don&apos;t often connect with Mary Balogh books, and this one seemed <b>way</b> over the top to me. Fleur and Adam were probably made for each other, but I really didn&apos;t care. I will summarize the book below.<br/><br/>She: I ran away from a bad thing, I have no money, I must sell myself to survive, <b>someone takes me up on it</b>, I find out my employer is also my defiler (who I <b>chose</b> to sell my body to), <b>I HATE YOU</b>.<br/><br/>He: I&apos;m scarred, I scare everyone, the woman I loved deeply/am married to has never lov</span>
  <span id="freeText4258393486388175481" style="display:none">3 stars<br /><br />I find that I don't often connect with Mary Balogh books, and this one seemed <b>way</b> over the top to me. Fleur and Adam were probably made for each other, but I really didn't care. I will summarize the book below.<br /><br />She: I ran away from a bad thing, I have no money, I must sell myself to survive, <b>someone takes me up on it</b>, I find out my employer is also my defiler (who I <b>chose</b> to sell my body to), <b>I HATE YOU</b>.<br /><br />He: I'm scarred, I scare everyone, the woman I loved deeply/am married to has never loved me, the woman selling her body that I took up on her offer hates me, <b>I HATE ME</b>.<br /><br />Me: unh. Could you guys just bone, please. Maybe that would get you both over all this whinging.<br /><br />They bone. Several times in one night. One night that seems to have at least two dawns. (It's a very special night.)<br /><br />She: We've boned, I love you, I will never be your mistress, we can never see each other again as long as we both live, <b>I HATE YOU</b>.<br /><br />He: We've boned, I love you deeper than the ocean forever and ever, we can never be together because I'm married and I choose my daughter over you, <b>I HATE ME</b>.<br /><br />Me: oh, for pete's sake. Didn't the boning get that infernal "woe is me" out of your systems? Is this book almost over?<br /><br />She: there is a solution to our problems, I haven't seen you for over a year, I've thought about you every day, you're beautiful just the way you are, you are probably just here because of your deep sense of obligation, <b>I HATE YOU</b>. (But really I love you.)<br /><br />He: I've missed you every day, you probably don't even remember my name, you definitely don't love me, our path has been too difficult, <b>I LOVE YOU</b>. (But you probably hate me.)<br /><br />Me: And they lived happily ever after. Thank <b>goodness</b> this is over. (And I really liked his daughter.)</span>
  <a data-text-id="4258393486388175481" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


