<div id="review_1964979780" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1964979780" />
    <a title="Heather" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4900066-heather"><img alt="Heather" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1465067550p2/4900066.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1964979780?book_show_action=true">Jan 14, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heather" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heather" href="/user/show/4900066-heather">Heather</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Heather by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/5684259-amy">Amy</a>
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4900066-heather?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4900066-heather?shelf=ill">ill</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1964979780" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14787888221928417021">Amy recommended this to me, so I wanted to like it, but I just couldn&apos;t. It was readable, but had so many of the flaws that I don&apos;t like in romances:<br/><br/>1) Heroine is the prettiest woman ever. All the men love her.<br/>2) Insta-love without apparent origin.<br/>3) Ridiculous extremes in feeling. She is disgusted/terrified with him. She hates him. Wait, she loves him. Nope, hates him again. Wait, eternal love! <br/>4) Barriers to love that are stupid and make me roll my eyes.<br/>5) Completely black and white characters</span>
  <span id="freeText14787888221928417021" style="display:none">Amy recommended this to me, so I wanted to like it, but I just couldn't. It was readable, but had so many of the flaws that I don't like in romances:<br /><br />1) Heroine is the prettiest woman ever. All the men love her.<br />2) Insta-love without apparent origin.<br />3) Ridiculous extremes in feeling. She is disgusted/terrified with him. She hates him. Wait, she loves him. Nope, hates him again. Wait, eternal love! <br />4) Barriers to love that are stupid and make me roll my eyes.<br />5) Completely black and white characters. <br /><br />I can get over some of this stuff in other romances, but this one was just not my cup of tea. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14787888221928417021" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


